snippet.textDisplay:
It's gone from about 36,000 cases per day up to about 100,000 cases per day over the last two weeks.    I have to admit that shocked me because I thought I would see about 50,000 per day.

Death of risen from about 125 per day to about 350 per day. That shocked me because it was 125. Deaths are rising steeply.

 Adjusting for state population, is particularly bad in Florida and Illinois. California has but highest case rate but they also have 38 million people

Based on prior trends, we could see as high as six hundred deaths per day in 2 weeks.

Almost all the deaths are among people with no vaccinations at all in the hospitalization by vaccination status databases that I looked at. But of course I'm not going to look at all 50 of them and some states don't maintain that data.

Since there's a correlation between age(65-plus), vaccination status, and political party affiliation, I think this might affect the elections.
